pTitle: Panasonic RP-HJE120-PPK In-Ear Headphone, Black
rText:
Best pair of earbuds you will ever own!
Pros:
~ Better than expensive market brands like Beats.( I prefer them over my $200 ATH-M50's)
~ They are incredibly comfortable, I've accidentally slept with them on several times!
~ The sound balance is great, not too much bass, all audiophiles will love them.
~ They're incredibly durable, I've had mine for a year and they still work.
Cons:
~ They're a tangle nightmare
~ The unboxing is quite underwhelming
rTitle: Best pair of earbuds you will ever own

Comfortable In-ear Design: 
The design was made based on geometric structure of ear, exactly fits and comforts the ears, and sound comes out concentrated only through the small size hole, which prevents sound from dispersion. 

Excellent sound:

One Button Control for Hands Free Calling: 
Unlike ordinary earbuds for daylily use, this comfort-fit earbuds allows for easy and accurate one-touch control to answer and end calls for hands free. 

Earphones Compatibility: 
Compatible with most Android phones, iPhone, iPad, iPod, Samsung Galaxy Phones, Tablets, Computers, MP3 Players, etc. 

Package Contains: 
1 Pack Earphones
1 Neck Strap

pTitle: Mizux IPhone Earbuds Premium In-Ear Wired Earphones with Microphone and Remote Control
rText:
My son needed a new pair of wired earbuds, so I decided to give this model a try. After trying them myself to make sure they functioned properly, I may have to buy myself a pair to keep in my school bag!

The earbuds came in a cute box. Upon opening it I noticed that, in addition to the earbuds, the box contained this silicone strap. After examining it I found that it's one of those bands that can be used to keep the earbuds around the neck. I decided to first just try the earbuds.

The buds themselves are very comfortable. Unlike most earbuds, they are not shaped round but kind of oval. They fit tightly and, most importantly, comfortably in my ear canal.

The volume control consists of a sliding button midway down the cord. Next to it is a “pause button”, which is very convenient as the music can be turned off without touching your phone.

I then tried the holder thing. Although it could be great for young children, I don't anticipate that I will use it.

The bass comes through surprisingly well. The volume, if at the highest setting, is louder than I can ever imagine needing it. Overall, the sound is really great.

I would definitely recommend these earbuds to anyone in the market for affordable, wired earbuds.
rTitle: Mizux Earbuds: A Good Value For Your Money

pTitle: Mizux IPhone Earbuds Premium In-Ear Wired Earphones with Microphone and Remote Control
rText: I originally bought these for my son who still likes to use the plug in earbuds with his phone when listening to music. His previous pair had been chewed through by our foster kittens. He wanted a white set so I bought these but I also bought a more traditional set with the more standard rubber earpieces that come in different sizes. He is really picky about how earbuds feel in his ears so he decided to use the other set and I, very lucky me, get to keep this one. As it turns out, these are very comfortable which was actually a surprise to me. The best thing about these, however, is the amazing sound quality. They get a really good seal in my ear and my music sounds incredible! For the price of these headphones, I honestly would not normally have very high expectations except the reviews were so good I decided it was worth buying them. Well, now I'm one of the super high reviews. This product is well worth buying.

rText:
I was surprised to see how big the earbuds are. They're shaped a little differently from most, so I gave them a try. It was uncomfortable, but I gave it an hour or so to see if they get better. Unfortunately, they really are just too big - the insides of my ears hurt, no matter how I adjust them. It might just be me - when I've used other buds with replaceable ear pad things, the smallest ones fit me the best. So if you don't have small ears, then maybe they'd be comfortable for you.

The sound quality is excellent. It was a huge difference between my old ones, so if it wasn't for the size/comfort thing, I'd definitely give these a great review.
rTitle: Great sound, but they were too big for my ears

pTitle: SENSO Bluetooth Headphones, Best Wireless Sports Earphones w/ Mic IPX7 Waterproof HD Stereo Sweatproof Earbuds for Gym Running Workout 8 Hour Battery Noise Cancelling Headsets
rText: I am so disappointed in these. They started out fine but after a short time the bluetooth connection goes in and out so much I finally took them off and pulled out my old wired ones. Specifically any time I go outside. I was hoping to use them while I was gardening or mowing the lawn. I tried them in my shorts pocket. Every time I would kneel down the sound would cut out. I eventually changed to a t-shirt that had a pocket on the chest and put my phone in that. Again it would still go in and out and say "Connected" over and over. Finally I even held the phone against the headphones just to see if that worked. Still I had problems. Inside the house seems fine but they're supposed to have a 30' range. I didn't even get a 3' range. And of course I've had them for about six weeks so it's too late to return them.

pTitle: SYCellular 3.5MM Wired Earphones Earbuds Headset Microphone with Carry case / Remote for ios android smartphone devices (White)
rText:
These are horrible. I don't understand all the great reviews bc I'm certainly not picky when it comes to sound quality and even I couldn't stand these.

At first I was hopeful bc they come packaged similar and look identical to the apple earbuds but as soon as I plugged them in I knew it wasn't to be. The sound is very muffled and is of very low quality. Honestly I could almost live with that but then I got a call--and my god I thought I was talking through a can with a string tied to the end--horrible. And the person on the other line actually hung up bc she thought we had a bad connection. It wasn't the connection these are just really bad quality earbuds. Sadly I've gotten better ones at 5 Below. I'm sending these back--skip these earbuds, buy something else. I'd give them 0 stars if I could

pTitle: Bluetooth Headphones, Hussar Magicbuds Best Wireless Sports Earphones with Mic, IPX7 Waterproof, HD Sound with Bass, Noise Cancelling, Secure Fit, up to 9 hours working time (Upgraded)
rText: I received these yesterday along with another set of Bluetooth earbuds by another company. These are by far the most comfortable for wearing over several hours, including while hiking & sweating. I have been a long time LG Infinum (sp?) user(they usually last at least 6 months), however assuming these hold up to heavy usage(lots of hours every day) I will be switching to these permanently. The quality of the sound is far better for music. I'm extremely impressed!! I usually remove my earbuds when seated and alone simply because my ears are not comfortable. Today, for the first time, I'm seated after a busy day and am listening to music on these earbuds as I write this review. I can't say enough positive about these very lightweight little buds! In addition, this is the first time I did not need to change the earbuds pieces to improve their fit in my ear. They are most definitely the best I've found at noise canceling. While out on the trail today, in fairly windy conditions, I actually found that I wished I could decrease the volume one more notch. This too is a first for me with headphones. I will update this review if these do not manage to hold up to my normal wear and tear. Here's hoping that they last. If you are waffling I feel they are worth the risk. The price point is among the least expensive with the best audio, etc that I've experienced.
rTitle: Very Good Sound, Noise Canceling, Light & Comfy!

pTitle: Bluetooth Headphones, Hussar Magicbuds Best Wireless Sports Earphones with Mic, IPX7 Waterproof, HD Sound with Bass, Noise Cancelling, Secure Fit, up to 9 hours working time (Upgraded)
rText: When I first got these headphones, I would have given them a five star. The sound is great, battery life is excellent, they have a far reach, they fit nicely, and they don't look too cumbersome in your ear. I have had them for a year now and am starting to have some issues, which maybe is to be expected for all wireless headphones by that time? The description of the headphones says that they are sweat-proof. I'm not sure if it is my sweat causing the outer layer of them to peel, or if it is simply from wear. At random times the music will cut in and out, or they will just completely shut off on me. Again, not sure if I have bionic sweat causing this issue, or if the headphones are just not the best quality. I guess for what I paid for them, I'm not too disappointed and got some good use out of them. But I will probably be buying a different brand to replace them and then decide how they compare.

pTitle: Bluetooth Headphones, Hussar Magicbuds Best Wireless Sports Earphones with Mic, IPX7 Waterproof, HD Sound with Bass, Noise Cancelling, Secure Fit, up to 9 hours working time (Upgraded)
rText: I really wanted to like these, because the sound they produce is amazing. The major issue with these headphones is the rubber ear wrap. If you are doing any type of moving around while working out they will fall off. You might be able to get by if you are just jogging, but any type of long distance and the sweat will cause them to fall. The other issue I have with them is that they don't work well in humid environments. I experienced Bluetooth connectivity issues while working out in a humid environment. The only way to resolve the issue is to hold your phone in your hand. I wouldn't complain about this if it weren't for the fact that other headphones I have had didn't have this problem (although they had other issues).

pTitle: In Ear Earphones, Tonicstar Wired Headphones with Microphone Clear Stereo Sound High Compatibility with Phone Tablet Computer MP3 Player
rText:
Pros: Great value. Sound quality is good, bass is good; comparable to my $40 Beats earbuds. Solid construction, a single Y split at the mic/remote. 3 sets of earbuds included.

Cons: Connector makes some noise if you turn it. Remote doesn't work with iPod shuffle.

Overall: the cons are irrelevant at the current price point ($8). If these were $30 earbuds, I would care, but for $8, I didn't even expect a remote, and connector issues don't happen while lifting unless I explicitly twist it around.

rText: These earbuds are of pretty decent quality material, with fair audio and mic performance. The buds are shaped a bit oddly, so they occasionally fall out of my ears, but that's pretty rare. The volume buttons work well, as does holding down the play/pause button. However, quickly pressing play/pause button doesn't seem to work. The round shape of the mic, combined with buttons that are flush with the edges, makes for controls that are difficult to feel for - I often have to look down at the controls to see where the buttons are. All in all these are quite functional, as long as you don't mind iffy play/pause functionality.

pTitle: Huawei In-Ear Earbuds Headphones with Microphone HiFi Stereo Sound Noise Cancelling Compatible with...
rText:
These are the most comfortable earbuds I have worn. I have had a dozen apple style earbuds over the years some apple some off brands all fairly cheap 10-20 dollar range. The sound is fine or similar to my previous earbuds, I'm no audiophile I just want to listen to podcasts and some music and these do the job. Someone said the switch is not tactile enough and I would agree but it's pretty long and a smash of the fingers my music pauses no problem. Turning it up or down takes a little more finesse. The build quality is very nice, once these break or get lost I will replace them with the same.

The part that goes into your ear is thick somewhat egg shaped and it fits snugly inside my ear instead of dangling. Very comfy, had my wife try them and she also thought they fit nice.
rTitle: These are the most comfortable earbuds I have worn

pTitle: Amazon Premium Headphones
rText: I love these headphones! I've been through 3 pair of Bose phones that sounded good but the cords made cheap and keep on breaking! I don't like the kind that go inside the ear canal because after a short while they begin to hurt. That being said I decided that I'd try these inexpensive Amazon ones because I spent 100.00 each for the Bose head buds. WOW these are great! They don't go into your ear too far and are very comfortable to wear for long periods of time without irritating your ear, they let in ambient sound so your not oblivious to what's going on around you which I like also! And the sound is awesome I think even better than the 100.00 Bose!! Great highs mids and decent bass! Definitely worth the money 💰

pTitle: Wireless Bluetooth Earbuds,CHSMONB Bluetooth Earphones Bluetooth Headset Mini Invisible Wireless Earphones Wireless Earbuds with Built in Mic for Gym Running Driving and Cooking,5 Hours Play Time.
rText:
Despite the description of the item as being multiple items you only get one.This is the title of the product when I bought it.
"Wireless Bluetooth Earbuds, CHSMONB Bluetooth Earphones Bluetooth Headset Mini Invisible Wireless Earphones Wireless Earbuds with Built in Mic for Gym Running Driving and Cooking,5 Hours Play Time"
It states in the title the word Earbuds twice. It also states Earphones twice. Not true! Not true at all! You get one earbud.
In the product description, it has 4 pictures of the product. Two of these pictures show two earbuds with one picture described as "The smallest mini Bluetooth earbuds" and the other as "Super dazzling LED effect when turn on the earbuds". 6 times this single item is described as dual earbuds and it's just not true. Am I the only one that thought I was getting two buds when I only got one?

pTitle: Bluetooth Headphones ZEUS OUTDOOR Wireless Earbuds HD Stereo Waterproof IPX7 Sweatproof Sports Earphones with Mic Best Wireless Headphones for Running Sport Workout Noise Cancelling Bluetooth Headset
rText:
Decent little set of Bluetooth headphones for the price, though not the most sturdy. I tossed these in a loose front pocket on a pair of running shorts, got to the gym to find out that one of the ear buds cracked off. Will try another brand to see how they hold up comparatively.

Positives:
- great price
- decent sound for the $
- holds a charge relatively well
- connected to my iPhone 7 without issues every time
- was never caught in downpour but held up to light rain

Suggested improvements:
- Sturdier connection between bud and earpiece (cracked off)
- adjust firmware for more intuitive audio and forward/reverse control wearing these, you press the back button to turn sound up or forward and the front button to lower volume or replay. Intuitively forward should be forward/increase volume --its reversed on these
- while the rubber wire connector looks nice with a matte like finish, it gets caught up in hair and pulls. I have shorter hair and this was still an issue. Ended up wearing the cable/wires in front to avoid this
- wind noise when biking, esp on windy day is really prevalent to the point of being annoying. I can't comment on whether or not this is unique to these, as it was my first set of Bluetooth buds.
- low volume doesn't go very low and then cuts out

Overall I was pleased with these for the value until they cracked in a non impact type situation. (Loose front pocket). I contacted Zeus and was offered 10% discount on another pair. Sorry but for that I will give another brand a shot.

pTitle: UCero Bluetooth Headphones, Wireless Headset V4.1 Heavy Bass Stereo In Ear Earbuds Noise Isolating Sweat proof Sports Earphones with Mic and Soft Security Hooks
rText:
I previously had TaoTronics bluetooth headphones which I really enjoyed but ended up giving them away. I was looking for a replacement, so I decided to try these out.
The sound quality is sub-par because the treble is way too high. Even after adjusting my phone's equalizer settings I couldn't get what I'd consider to be average sounding music. I could adjust bass and treble but the mid-range always sounded faint while the highs were always very loud in comparison.
I originally bought this headset for the design. I liked the two buttons on top (volume/track) versus the three buttons other models have where the multi-function button is in the middle. The multi-function button on this headset is on the side, which I would accidentally press while trying to push the unit into my ear for a more snug fit.
The volume up button increases the volume, but holding it down plays the previous track. Holding the volume down button plays the next track. This is opposite of other models where volume+ is associated with track+.
I thought the over-ear piece which keeps the headset around your ear isn't firm - it was a bit too bendable and large for my taste so it doesn't comfortably wrap around my ear.
I'm probably being too picky as these reasons might not be issues for other people and in time I'd probably get used to them. The high treble affecting the music was enough for me to return this headset. To be fair, I only listened to various songs for about five minutes before deciding to re-box and send back.
rTitle: High treble overshadows all other sound

pTitle: UCero Bluetooth Headphones, Wireless Headset V4.1 Heavy Bass Stereo In Ear Earbuds Noise Isolating Sweat proof Sports Earphones with Mic and Soft Security Hooks
rText:
This is my 3rd different brand of Bluetooth headphones. I have one pair that is 3 years old, so i was hoping to find a pair that would back those up. (My 2nd pair will only work inside, also a different brand). I just had the UCero on when i got a phone call from my Mom. We talked for an hour. She just turned 80 and i told her i had the headphones on when we talked. At the end of the call, she said i sounded fine the entire time. She said if i hadn't said anything, should not have noticed. For me though, talking to hear, occasionally i'd hear like a metal distortion noise, but i could still understand her. It was enough times it was a bit annoying, but she never heard anything wrong.
The overall sound was great, they have just the right amount of bass, gotta have base. But i could hear static inbetween songs; the volume wasn't too high either. I noticed it when i was streaming Spotify, so i tried to stored music on my phone and i heard it again.
If i could i'd give these a score of 3.75 out of 5. The sound is great, fits great and sound quality for someone i'm talking to is great. But the tiny sound on a call and the static between songs was just a bummer.
I'll still keep these as a back up set.
rTitle: Great sound, but a couple cons

pTitle: UCero Bluetooth Headphones, Wireless Headset V4.1 Heavy Bass Stereo In Ear Earbuds Noise Isolating Sweat proof Sports Earphones with Mic and Soft Security Hooks
rText:
I was not nearly as impressed with these headphones as a lot of these other people. I wanted headphones that would stay on my ears securely when I worked out, so I got these for $15 on a lightning deal and disliked them so much that I returned them after 1 workout.

I have had a pair of Taotronics headphones for the last several years (https://www.amazon.com/TaoTronics-Bluetooth-Headphones-Sweatproof-Cancellation/dp/B06WP5DBMQ/ref=sr_1_9?ie=UTF8&qid=1493945560&sr=8-9&keywords=taotronics+headphones), and they have worked fairly well for me. My only issue was that the anatomy of my ear makes it easy for those headphones to fall out (I don't have much of an anti-tragus - I promise that's a thing, look it up). I thought the piece extending around the ear on the Ucero's would make it a good choice - not so fast, but we'll get to that.

The most egregious flaw in these headphones was that the bluetooth connection would cut out for ~1 second randomly throughout my workout - so distracting that it ruined my flow. The sound quality seemed pretty decent when I manually pressed the headphone into my ear, but unfortunately I could not get a good fit without literally pushing the headphone into my ear and holding it there - despite my perception that this design would provide a better fit than my current headphones. I tried the various sized ear pieces to no avail, and the hook around the ear was a bit too big (although I have big ears) which made the earpiece flop around my ear with any significant movement (aka, working out).

I cannot comment on the battery life because I already passed the "deal breaker" threshold long before the battery even got low enough to require its first charge.

Overall, these headphones might work well for someone else (and in regards to some of my criticisms, maybe I just got a bad pair?), but I would rather spend 2-3x this money and get headphones that work. These headphones did have some redeeming factors, but especially when it comes to the poor connectivity, buying these headphones for me is akin to buying a car with seats that are kind of uncomfortable and doesn't always run, but it drives so well when it works! Sorry guys, not enough for me! Returned after a single use!
rTitle: Has some redeeming qualities, but too many issues for me

pTitle: KOTION EACH B3505 Wireless NFC Stereo USB 3.5mm Plug Bluetooth Gaming Headphone Headset with Mic for iPhone 6S Plus 6 5 5s 5c ,Ipad ,Lenono,Samsung ,Blackberry, HTC, Sony, LG ,Tablet PC - Black/Orange
rText: I have had these for almost 2 years using them 24 hours + a week. The charge lasts a very long time. I use them at work to listen to audio books mostly but also music. I easily make it through a 8 hour shift without charging and I only charge them in the car in transport. I've even forgot to charge them and made it through a second day. I work construction so they are durable, currently covered in paint and mortar. They become uncomfortable after 4+ hours but I just take them off for 30 min them continue. I've never had a problem pairing them with the iPhone. I still have these in working order, but the charging port recently started acting up. I have to wiggle the cord ect. Probably from years of dust and abuse. I bought a much more expensive main brand pair of bluetooth headphones thinking i use them so much why not. I was wrong. The comfort and durability feel is slightly better on my new ones. But the side controls, battery life, sound quality, and pairing all take a back seat to these. Even the durability..they have a plastic feel but they are durable. I've dropped them many times, covered them in dust, even thrown them in my tool box, gotten them wet a few times..they did stop working for a few hours when i got them really wet but started agian after drying. I even took a bath watching a movie on my kindle and accedently submerged them 100% and they worked agian. I will be reordering these especially at the price

rText:
I actually just bought these for the bluetooth aspect and just for music when I commute to work. They work great. Fit snug but the padding on the pads are actually very soft. (not firm like alot of others)
Battery life is pretty impressive so far. I've had them for two weeks and only needed to charge them once so far (charge time is about 2hrs 30mins give or take) But I used them straight out of box, my phone registered them at 90% power so I just kept using them. It believe it says about 10hrs playback? (i could be wrong, go check it yourself). I was able to use them a solid 6 1/2 days out of box before I had to charge them. My usage is when I commute to work and home (about 50mins combined) and I use them at work sparingly (maybe 3 hrs a day on and off). So given those numbers, I was impressed it lasted me that long.

It should be noted though, I used them with a Iphone and it does say the battery life in % on my phone. But I'm not sure how occurate it is. It was on 90% for like 2-3 days and I was like this cant be right. Then on the 4-5day it went down to 70%, then on the 5th, it went to 50%, and on the last day it was at 30%, then it finally died. The number never went down lower than 30% until it died.. so maybe its just a good estimate. The headphones however did warn me for about a good 10 mins with beeping noises once in while, indicating the battery was about to give out. I will have to monitor it now on 1st charge to see if it goes out around 30%.

other than that, its nice headphones, cheap and they sound pretty decent. I have beats, and they are better, no doubt, but not 175$ better. For the price, i would strongly recommend these. They also come with wire if you run out of batteries to hook it up to your phone.
rTitle: I just use this as a normal headphone set and not for gaming.
